<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Two species groups can be recognized in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Afroheriades" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afroheriades" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afroheriades</taxonomicName>
: one includes a rather robust form with the basal area of propodeum well below the level of the scutellum [
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Afroheriades" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afroheriades primus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="primus">Afroheriades primus</taxonomicName>
(Peters)]; the other includes the remaining species, which have a more elongate mesosoma and the base of the propodeum at the same plane as the scutellum. If a phylogenetic analysis shows that these two groups are natural, they could be subgenerically separated as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Afroheriades" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afroheriades" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afroheriades</taxonomicName>
s.str. and 
<taxonomicName authority="Peters, 1978" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Archeriades" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Archeriades" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Archeriades</taxonomicName>
, as suggested by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Michener (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. For now, we treat them as species groups. Below are the species currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Afroheriades" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afroheriades" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afroheriades</taxonomicName>
; the synonyms presented here are based on the study 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="68" start="start">of</pageBreakToken>
the types by the senior author. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Afroheriades" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afroheriades capensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">Afroheriades capensis</taxonomicName>
Griswold, in Michener (2007: 452), is a nomen nudum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
